<div class="donation-header">
  <h2>DONATION PROCESS</h2>
  <div class="divider">
    <span class="line"></span>
    <span class="blood-icon"></span>
    <span class="line"></span>
  </div>
  <p>The donation process from the time you arrive center until the time you leave!</p>
</div>

<section class="donation-process">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="steps">
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-image">
          <img src="/images/process_1.jpg" alt="Registration">
          <span class="step-number">1</span>
        </div>
        <h3>Registration</h3>
        <p>
          You need to complete a very simple registration form. 
          It collects your contact details and basic health information. 
          This ensures our staff can safely process your donation and keep track of your records.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-image">
          <img src="/images/process_2.jpg" alt="Screening">
          <span class="step-number">2</span>
        </div>
        <h3>Screening</h3>
        <p>
          A small drop of blood from your finger will be tested. 
          This checks your hemoglobin and iron levels to confirm that it is safe for you to donate. 
          The process is quick and ensures your safety during the donation.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-image">
          <img src="/images/process_3.jpg" alt="Donation">
          <span class="step-number">3</span>
        </div>
        <h3>Donation</h3>
        <p>
          Once screening is complete, you will be guided to a comfortable donor bed. 
          The actual blood donation takes about 6-10 minutes. 
          Our trained staff will ensure the process is safe, hygienic, and comfortable for you.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-image">
          <img src="/images/process_4.jpg" alt="Refreshment">
          <span class="step-number">4</span>
        </div>
        <h3>Refreshment</h3>
        <p>
          After donation, you can relax in the sitting area and enjoy some refreshments. 
          This helps you recover and ensures you feel strong before leaving the center. 
          It's our way of thanking you for your generous donation.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>